Waverton Investment Management Ltd. Key Developments

Waverton Investment Management Appoints Mark Harrison as Chief Operating Officer
Jan 17 17
Waverton Investment Management has appointed Mark Harrison as chief operating officer. Harrison previously held senior executive positions at PwC, BNP Paribas, JP Morgan Cazenove, AMP and EFG Bank.


Waverton Investment Management Limited Announces Earnings Results for the Nine Months Ended June 30, 2016
Sep 14 16
Waverton Investment Management Limited announced earnings results for the nine months ended June 30, 2016. For the period, the company records pre-tax income of £5.5 million against £6.3 million a year ago.


Waverton Investment Management Ltd. Announces Financial Results for the Six Months Ended March 31, 2016
Jun 10 16
Waverton Investment Management Ltd. announced financial results for the six months ended March 31, 2016. For the six month, the company reported revenue of £15.8 million against £16.0 million a year ago. EBITDA of £3.8 million against £5.2 million a year ago. Profit before tax of £3.7 million against £4.8 million a year ago. The year on year financial results were impacted by a lower AuM driven by weaker capital markets and increased property costs due to Waverton moving into new premises in September 2015.


