Waverton Investment Management Ltd. »
Waverton is an active manager that follows a flexible, pragmatic approach, being open to new themes and ideas, instead of being beholden to a particular philosophy.The firm invests in equities and fixed-income on a global basis.  Company visits are an essential part of the investment process and fund managers visit North America, Continental Europe and Asia several times a year.The stock selection committee meets weekly to monitor and review investment ideas and make portfolio changes. An asset allocation meeting also meets monthly to review macroeconomic, political and other global trends that may affect any decision making process over and above stock selection.Waverton aims to achieve capital growth and dividend income. Research is provided by external institutions. The investment process is bottom-up, and the key indicators monitored include: management that is rewarded for the good performance of the company; market leadership; operation in an industry that has significant barriers to entry; and large market potential. Investment decisions are taken by the individual fund managers, who specialize geographically.The firm tailors each investment portfolio to the client's financial needs and believes that the way to achieve superior returns over the long-term is not to be constrained by excessive benchmarking or overly rigid asset allocation parameters. The investment team is driven by individual stock ideas, but the firm is not afraid to make significant judgment calls about asset classes. They believe that qualitative evaluation of a company's prospects is more important than 'number crunching' and that preserving this emphasis on quality protects clients' assets in difficult times.






